item.description:
@_bool wrote:

[quote=“Razr`, post:16, topic:235395”]A variable is a piece of data that can change.

Now that you’ve learned that, I should tell you that …

if(objectID == 3192);

isn’t a valid statement, remove it.[/quote]
That’s a perfectly fine statement,
It doesn’t do anything, but it’s a valid statement.

item.title: Yet another Unfixable Error
item.dc:creator: @x_blitz_x x blitz x
item.description:
@x_blitz_x wrote:

[quote=“Razr`, post:16, topic:235395”]A variable is a piece of data that can change.

Now that you’ve learned that, I should tell you that …

if(objectID == 3192);

isn’t a valid statement, remove it.[/quote]

You are wrong. That is a valid statement, it means that the if statement does not have a body. It would compile and run but the if statement wouldn’t do anything. Think of it like a place holder for a future if statement.

Read full topic
